WEBVTT

00:31.932 --> 00:33.301
GOLD PRESENT
AND ACCOUNTED FOR.

00:33.367 --> 00:34.602
CHECK!

00:34.668 --> 00:36.670
GOLD STACK,
STANDARD MILITARY--
10 ROWS HIGH,

00:36.737 --> 00:38.872
5 BARS DEEP?
CHECK.

00:38.939 --> 00:40.108
[CLATTER]

00:40.174 --> 00:42.042
WHAT WAS THAT?

00:45.913 --> 00:48.382
[WHIMPERING]

00:48.449 --> 00:49.583
AAH!

00:50.851 --> 00:51.952
[GRUNTING]

00:52.019 --> 00:53.787
OH!

00:53.854 --> 00:56.190
AAH!

01:00.060 --> 01:01.262
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:01.329 --> 01:03.063
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:03.131 --> 01:05.499
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:05.566 --> 01:06.967
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:07.034 --> 01:08.836
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:08.902 --> 01:11.472
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:11.539 --> 01:13.006
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:13.073 --> 01:14.375
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

01:14.442 --> 01:17.411
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:17.478 --> 01:19.046
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:19.113 --> 01:20.414
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:20.481 --> 01:23.351
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:25.153 --> 01:26.787
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

01:26.854 --> 01:29.357
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

01:30.891 --> 01:35.263
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

01:35.329 --> 01:36.897
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:36.964 --> 01:38.366
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:38.432 --> 01:40.968
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:41.034 --> 01:42.470
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:42.536 --> 01:44.138
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:44.205 --> 01:47.007
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:47.074 --> 01:48.709
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:48.776 --> 01:50.043
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:50.110 --> 01:52.746
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

01:52.813 --> 01:57.117
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:00.588 --> 02:02.356
Daphne: THIS DOESN'T
LOOK LIKE FORT KNOX.

02:02.423 --> 02:04.292
Velma: FORT KNOX
IS UP AHEAD.

02:04.358 --> 02:05.959
THESE ARE JUST
A BUNCH OF BUSINESSES

02:06.026 --> 02:07.328
LOOKING TO MAKE
AN EASY BUCK

02:07.395 --> 02:09.263
OFF UNSUSPECTING TOURISTS.

02:09.330 --> 02:12.666
NO WAY! THE GOLD-ADE
DRINK FACTORY!

02:12.733 --> 02:14.468
FRED, STOP THE VAN!

02:14.535 --> 02:16.504
MAYBE ON THE WAY BACK,
SHAG.

02:16.570 --> 02:20.274
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO MEET
MR. B. AND THE SECRET
6 PUPPIES AT THE FORT.

02:20.341 --> 02:22.510
I HOPE WE CAN ACTUALLY
SEE THE GOLD.

02:22.576 --> 02:25.413
IT'S POSSIBLE. MR. B.
IS FRIENDS WITH THE GENERAL.

02:25.479 --> 02:28.282
LIKE, ARE WE TALKING
A LOT OF GOLD?

02:28.349 --> 02:29.717
MORE THAN A LOT.

02:29.783 --> 02:32.486
MOST OF AMERICA'S GOLD
IS STORED AT FORT KNOX.

02:32.553 --> 02:34.955
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN
IN TERMS OF...PIZZAS?

02:35.022 --> 02:38.158
ENOUGH FOR YOU AND SCOOBY
NEVER TO GO HUNGRY AGAIN.

02:38.226 --> 02:39.993
MM-MM!

02:40.060 --> 02:42.830
HURRY, FRED!
Man: HALT!

02:42.896 --> 02:45.266
HELLO, OFFICER.
WE'RE HERE TO SEE
MR. B.

02:45.333 --> 02:47.435
AND THE SECRET
6 PUPPIES.

02:47.501 --> 02:48.636
FRIENDS OF THE GENERAL.

02:48.702 --> 02:49.870
MAY I SEE YOUR PASS?

02:49.937 --> 02:51.572
WE DON'T HAVE A PASS.

03:09.690 --> 03:12.526
[SCOOBY GIGGLES]

03:15.829 --> 03:17.865
WHAT'S THIS?

03:18.999 --> 03:20.934
SO THAT'S WHERE
YOU KEEP YOUR

03:21.001 --> 03:22.536
"IN CASE OF EMERGENCY
STASH."

03:22.603 --> 03:24.705
HEY, KIDS,
GLAD YOU MADE IT!

03:24.772 --> 03:28.276
I KNEW IT WAS YOU,
'CAUSE EVERYONE ELSE HERE
SHAVES THEIR HEAD.

03:28.342 --> 03:30.143
THERE HE IS!
YES, SIR.

03:30.210 --> 03:31.579
SOLDIER, THESE CIVILIANS
HAVE CLEARANCE.

03:31.645 --> 03:36.517
GIVE THEM THE ALMOST
ALL-ACCESS PASSES.

03:36.584 --> 03:39.287
Drill Sergeant: PREPARE
MID-AFTERNOON EXERCISES!

03:39.353 --> 03:41.221
LIKE, DOES HE MEAN
SIT-UPS?

03:41.289 --> 03:42.656
NOT EXACTLY.

03:42.723 --> 03:45.459
[EXPLOSIONS]

03:45.526 --> 03:47.761
JEEPERS! YOU'D THINK
THE NEIGHBORS WOULD COMPLAIN.

03:47.828 --> 03:50.264
EVEN IF THEY DID,
YOU WOULDN'T HEAR THEM.

03:50.331 --> 03:52.466
I APOLOGIZE
FOR THE SEARCH
AND SEIZURE.

03:52.533 --> 03:55.168
WE'VE HAD TO INCREASE
SECURITY LATELY.

03:55.235 --> 03:56.704
ENEMY SPIES?

03:56.770 --> 03:57.871
GOLD MONSTER.

03:57.938 --> 03:59.340
PERMISSION TO GULP, SIR?

03:59.407 --> 04:00.374
PERMISSION GRANTED.

04:00.441 --> 04:01.709
[GULP]
[GULP]

04:01.775 --> 04:03.176
A GOLD MONSTER?

04:03.243 --> 04:04.778
MAYBE. I DON'T KNOW.

04:04.845 --> 04:07.915
BUT I DO KNOW
SOMETHING TURNED
2 OF MY BEST GUARDS

04:07.981 --> 04:09.350
INTO GOLD STATUES.

04:09.417 --> 04:10.918
ARE THE PUPPIES OK?

04:10.984 --> 04:12.420
SEE FOR YOURSELF.

04:12.486 --> 04:14.788
* WE ARE ARMY,
WE WORK HARD *

04:14.855 --> 04:16.724
[RUFF RUFF RUFF
RUFF RUFF RUFF RUFF]

04:16.790 --> 04:19.493
* AND WE DON'T MESS
IN THE NEIGHBOR'S YARD *

04:19.560 --> 04:21.429
[RUFF RUFF RUFF RUFF
RUFF RUFF RUFF]

04:21.495 --> 04:24.598
COMPANY...HALT!

04:24.665 --> 04:27.435
WOW, TALK ABOUT
WELL-TRAINED.

04:27.501 --> 04:28.669
WATCH THIS.

04:38.111 --> 04:39.513
THEY'RE GOOD!

04:41.415 --> 04:43.684
ALL THANKS
TO DRILL SERGEANT
PAYNE.

04:43.751 --> 04:46.387
HE'S THE MOST ARMY MAN
ON THIS BASE,

04:46.454 --> 04:47.721
FROM THE BUZZ
OF HIS BUZZ CUT

04:47.788 --> 04:49.523
TO THE SHINE
OF HIS SHINY SHOES.

04:49.590 --> 04:51.725
MAN, LIKE EVEN
WATCHING FIELD
EXERCISES

04:51.792 --> 04:53.561
MAKES ME HUNGRY.

04:53.627 --> 04:54.662
ME, TOO!

04:54.728 --> 04:56.697
GO TO THE MESS HALL.
YOU CAN GRAB CHOW

04:56.764 --> 04:58.999
IN THE GREEN BUILDING
AROUND THE CORNER.

05:01.802 --> 05:03.136
UH...WHICH ONE?

05:03.203 --> 05:05.639
LIKE, I GUESS
THE GREEN ONE.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.511
ALL RIGHT, SCOOB.
NOW WE'RE COOKIN'.

05:10.578 --> 05:12.546
AND I HOPE
THEY ARE, TOO.

05:12.613 --> 05:14.682
LOOK, SCOOB,
A HIGH-TECH HAND WASHER.

05:14.748 --> 05:17.418
OH, WE MUST BE GETTING
CLOSE TO THE CHOW.

05:20.187 --> 05:22.556
OOH! CLEAN!

05:26.326 --> 05:27.695
"GOLD LEVEL"?

05:27.761 --> 05:29.797
LIKE, THAT MUST BE
WHERE THE GENERALS
EAT.

05:41.174 --> 05:43.944
HEY, LIKE I THOUGHT
THIS WAS AN ALL-ACCESS
PASS.

05:44.011 --> 05:46.580
"ALMOST"? OH, MAN!

05:46.647 --> 05:49.116
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

05:51.552 --> 05:52.820
GOOD WORK, SCOOB.

05:55.989 --> 05:59.026
WE WENT THROUGH
ALL OF THAT FOR GOLD?

05:59.092 --> 06:02.430
GOLD? OH...PHOOEY!

06:02.496 --> 06:05.433
LIKE, IF IT WERE
A BOAT-SIZED BANANA SPLIT

06:05.499 --> 06:08.702
WITH EXTRA CHEESE SAUCE,
SURE. BUT GOLD?

06:10.971 --> 06:12.506
AAH!
AAH!

06:17.010 --> 06:19.980
SCOOB! AN ESCAPE BUTTON!
WE'RE SAVED!

06:20.047 --> 06:24.051
[ALARM BLARES]

06:30.458 --> 06:31.959
WE HEARD THE ALARM.

06:32.025 --> 06:33.861
NOW, WHERE'D HE GO?

06:33.927 --> 06:35.028
WHERE'D WHO GO?

06:35.095 --> 06:38.432
THE CREEPY GOLD GUY
WITH NO FACE.

06:38.499 --> 06:40.133
IS EVERYONE OK?

06:40.200 --> 06:41.735
[GIGGLING]

06:41.802 --> 06:42.936
WE ARE NOW.

06:43.003 --> 06:44.938
IT SURE WAS GENEROUS
OF THE GENERAL

06:45.005 --> 06:46.874
TO LET US STAY WITH
THE SECRET 6.

06:46.940 --> 06:50.177
BUT WHO CAN SLEEP
WHEN THERE'S A GOLDEN
GHOUL RUNNING LOOSE?

06:50.243 --> 06:52.079
NOT ME. LET'S GO
LOOK AROUND.

06:52.145 --> 06:53.681
LIKE, YOU GUYS
GO AHEAD.

06:53.747 --> 06:55.516
WE'RE GONNA HELP
THE PUPPIES WITH
MAKING THEIR BEDS--

06:55.583 --> 06:56.984
THE ARMY WAY.

06:57.050 --> 06:58.886
TIGHT!

07:01.054 --> 07:04.391
I WANNA BLEND IN
SO I CAN SURPRISE
THE MONSTER.

07:04.458 --> 07:06.226
I'LL BET HE WON'T EVEN
SEE YOU COMING.

07:06.293 --> 07:07.561
THERE HE IS!

07:09.463 --> 07:11.231
I GOT HIM! I GOT HIM!

07:11.298 --> 07:12.966
UH...I DON'T THINK SO.

07:13.033 --> 07:15.936
YOU'VE ACTUALLY CAPTURED
TRAVIS KNOX, SIR!

07:16.003 --> 07:18.672
HE SNEAKS ON BASE
ALL THE TIME, SIR!

07:18.739 --> 07:21.575
YOU CAN'T
CAPTURE ME.
I OWN THIS LAND.

07:21.642 --> 07:23.644
WHY DO YOU THINK
THEY NAMED IT
FORT KNOX?

07:23.711 --> 07:26.113
I VOW HERE AND NOW

07:26.179 --> 07:28.516
I WILL RECLAIM MY LAND!

07:30.551 --> 07:32.385
AND DON'T THINK
YOU'LL GET MY STORE, TOO!

07:32.452 --> 07:34.121
I HAVE AN ALARM SYSTEM.

07:34.187 --> 07:35.656
GOOD WORK, SIR!

07:35.723 --> 07:38.158
THANKS. I LIKE MEDALS.

07:40.961 --> 07:42.996
Drill Sergeant:
READY NIGHT-TIME
EXERCISES!

07:43.063 --> 07:43.997
FIRE!

07:44.064 --> 07:46.166
[BOOM, BOOM]

07:50.037 --> 07:52.239
YAGGY! YAGGY!

07:52.305 --> 07:53.874
[GRUNTS]

07:57.010 --> 07:59.813
CAN OPENER? HA HA!
FINALLY, A MIDNIGHT
SNACK.

07:59.880 --> 08:01.214
[GASPS]

08:01.281 --> 08:03.383
THE SECRET 6!

08:03.450 --> 08:06.654
THEY'RE GONE!
[GRUNTING]

08:06.720 --> 08:09.489
HURRY, SCOOB.
WE'VE GOT TO FIND
THE PUPPIES.

08:10.891 --> 08:12.826
OK, SCOOBY.
DO YOUR STUFF.

08:12.893 --> 08:14.061
[SNIFF]

08:14.127 --> 08:17.865
GOOD WORK, SCOOB.
LET'S GO GET SOME PUPPIES.

08:21.935 --> 08:24.271
AAH!

08:25.873 --> 08:27.875
LIKE...[NERVOUS LAUGH]

08:27.941 --> 08:29.977
I'VE NEVER BEEN SO AFRAID
OF MY OWN FACE!

08:30.043 --> 08:31.979
REAH, SCARY!

08:35.916 --> 08:38.919
LOOK! SHAGGY AND SCOOBY
ARE IN TROUBLE.

08:40.053 --> 08:41.154
THERE YA GO, SCOOB.

08:42.990 --> 08:43.924
TANKS!

08:43.991 --> 08:44.925
YOU'RE WELCOME.

08:44.992 --> 08:47.160
NO--TANKS!

08:48.328 --> 08:49.930
AAH!
AAH!

08:55.235 --> 08:57.671
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

09:01.508 --> 09:04.277
WHAT'S GOING ON
OUT HERE?

09:04.344 --> 09:05.646
IS MY HELICOPTER OK?

09:05.713 --> 09:07.480
THE HELICOPTER'S GREAT.

09:07.547 --> 09:08.649
WHEW!

09:08.716 --> 09:10.417
BUT THE PUPPIES
ARE MISSING.

09:10.483 --> 09:11.719
THEY'RE MISSING?

09:11.785 --> 09:13.520
WHAT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

09:13.587 --> 09:16.323
WE JUST WOKE UP AND,
LIKE, THEY WERE GONE.

09:16.389 --> 09:17.490
[CLATTER]

09:17.557 --> 09:20.794
SECRET 6!

09:20.861 --> 09:25.699
Daphne: LOOK! THE MONSTER TURNED
DRILL SERGEANT PAYNE TO GOLD!

09:25.766 --> 09:29.870
ANOTHER ONE? AW, I AM
RUNNING OUT OF SOLDIERS!

09:31.371 --> 09:32.339
HMM...

09:32.405 --> 09:33.841
[WHIMPERING]

09:33.907 --> 09:35.809
RIGHT, SCOOB.
LIKE, WE HAVE TO
FIND THE PUPPIES

09:35.876 --> 09:37.477
BEFORE THE GOLD
MONSTER DOES.

09:37.544 --> 09:40.848
WE'LL START BACK
AT THE BARRACKS
AND LOOK FOR CLUES.

09:43.016 --> 09:45.819
Daphne: WELL, I THINK
I FOUND A CLUE.

09:45.886 --> 09:48.722
HUH? LIKE, THEY WEREN'T
THERE EARLIER.

09:48.789 --> 09:51.391
Fred: LOOK, GANG.
DIRT ON THEIR PAWS.

09:51.458 --> 09:53.727
I WONDER WHAT
THAT MEANS.

09:53.794 --> 09:55.562
[BUGLER PLAYS REVEILLE]

09:55.629 --> 09:58.165
WELL, I GUESS FORT KNOX
IS OPEN FOR BUSINESS.

09:58.231 --> 10:00.734
DRILL SERGEANT PAYNE
HAD A SECURITY BADGE

10:00.801 --> 10:02.736
FOR A SECRET DEVICE
DEVELOPMENT LAB.

10:02.803 --> 10:04.972
I THINK WE SHOULD
CHECK OUT THAT LAB.

10:05.038 --> 10:07.040
RIGHT. AND WHILE
WE DO THAT,

10:07.107 --> 10:10.043
SHAGGY, YOU AND SCOOBY
TAKE THE PUPS INTO TOWN

10:10.110 --> 10:12.713
AND CHECK OUT
THAT LOCAL LOONY,
TRAVIS KNOX.

10:12.780 --> 10:14.181
GOOD IDEA, FRED.

10:14.247 --> 10:16.750
THEN WE CAN ALSO HIT
THE GOLD-ADE FACTORY

10:16.817 --> 10:18.719
AND SEARCH FOR
SUSPICIOUS SOFT DRINKS.

10:18.786 --> 10:21.822
YUM--AHEM. YEAH!

10:27.961 --> 10:32.199
WILL YOU SIGN THIS PETITION
TO GIVE FORT KNOX BACK
TO ITS RIGHTFUL OWNER?

10:32.265 --> 10:34.534
ARE YOU TRAVIS KNOX?

10:34.601 --> 10:36.103
YEP. JUST LIKE
THE FORT.

10:36.169 --> 10:39.572
SURE. WE'LL SIGN.
LIKE, IS THE GOLD
YOURS, TOO?

10:39.639 --> 10:40.640
GOLD?

10:40.708 --> 10:41.875
YEAH, LIKE THERE'S

10:41.942 --> 10:44.011
A GIGANTIC PILE
OF GOLD IN THERE.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.214
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

10:47.280 --> 10:50.117
FIRST THEY TAKE
MY LAND, AND NOW
THEY TAKE MY GOLD?!

10:50.183 --> 10:51.584
I LOVE GOLD!

10:51.651 --> 10:53.520
AND I LOVE MY LAND!

10:53.586 --> 10:55.422
OH, THEY'VE GONE
TOO FAR!

10:55.488 --> 10:56.824
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING
AT?!

10:56.890 --> 10:59.827
THOSE SMOOTHIES
SURE LOOK GOOD.

10:59.893 --> 11:02.029
THAT'LL BE $27,
PLEASE.

11:05.298 --> 11:09.136
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN THE SECRET
DEVELOPMENT LAB?

11:09.202 --> 11:11.805
TRYING TO SOLVE
THE GOLD MONSTER
MYSTERY.

11:11.872 --> 11:13.807
WE MIGHT ASK YOU
THE SAME QUESTION.

11:13.874 --> 11:15.809
I AM THE GENERAL
IN CHARGE OF EVERYTHING

11:15.876 --> 11:17.610
AND AUTHORIZED
TO BE ANYWHERE!

11:17.677 --> 11:19.046
GOOD ANSWER.

11:20.547 --> 11:22.382
HEY, THESE FIT NICELY.

11:22.449 --> 11:23.851
WHAT DO THEY DO--OH!

11:23.917 --> 11:26.787
WOW! I CAN SEE
OUR BARRACKS
FROM UP HERE!

11:26.854 --> 11:29.156
WHAT'S THIS, GENERAL?

11:29.222 --> 11:30.657
DON'T TOUCH THAT!

11:30.724 --> 11:32.793
IT'S OUR MOST
TOP-SECRET DEVICE--

11:32.860 --> 11:34.527
SHUT-DOWN GOO.

11:34.594 --> 11:37.865
IT'S AN EXPANDABLE NET
THAT TRAPS ANYTHING
IT COVERS.

11:37.931 --> 11:40.968
SHUT-DOWN GOO? HMM...

11:41.034 --> 11:42.069
UH...

11:42.135 --> 11:45.105
DO YOU HAVE ANY
"HELP FRED DOWN" GOO?

11:47.875 --> 11:49.810
BOY, DO I LOVE GOLD-ADE.

11:49.877 --> 11:51.745
THEN AGAIN, EVERYONE DOES.

11:51.812 --> 11:54.514
[GLASS TINKLING]

11:54.581 --> 11:56.183
WELL, HELLO, STRANGERS.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.919
I'M SUE CROSE,
OWNER OF GOLD-ADE
SOFT DRINKS

11:58.986 --> 12:01.889
AND CLEANER
OF BROKEN GLASS.
CAN I HELP YOU?

12:01.955 --> 12:04.491
LIKE, WE'RE JUST HERE
TO DRINK AS MUCH
GOLD-ADE

12:04.557 --> 12:06.226
AS HUMANLY
AND DOGGEDLY POSSIBLE.

12:06.293 --> 12:09.096
WELL, YOU'RE IN LUCK.
LOOKS LIKE I GOT 2 LEFT.

12:11.932 --> 12:14.968
LIKE, CAN I JUST SAY
THAT I LOVE GOLD-ADE?

12:15.035 --> 12:17.637
WELL, SUGAR, IF THAT
CRAZY ARMY DOESN'T
KNOCK IT OFF

12:17.704 --> 12:19.940
WITH THOSE EXPLOSION
EXERCISES,

12:20.007 --> 12:22.442
THERE WON'T BE ANY MORE
GOLD-ADE FOR YOU
TO LOVE.

12:22.509 --> 12:24.812
EVERY HOUR--BOOM!

12:24.878 --> 12:26.379
UH-OH. HOLD ON.
WHAT FOR?

12:26.446 --> 12:28.281
NOON-TIME EXERCISES.

12:28.348 --> 12:30.383
[EXHALES]
THESE ARE DOOZIES.

12:30.450 --> 12:33.286
[BOOM, BOOM, BOOM]

12:34.087 --> 12:36.456
HOW LONG DOES THIS LAST?

12:36.523 --> 12:39.126
SORRY.
WE DON'T SELL GAS.

12:40.093 --> 12:42.062
LIKE, WHERE
ARE THE PUPS?

12:42.129 --> 12:43.496
[YIP YIP]

12:46.566 --> 12:49.736
IF THEY DON'T STOP
THOSE EVERY HOUR
BOOM BOOMS,

12:49.803 --> 12:52.205
I WILL HAVE TO
SHUT DOWN GOLD-ADE.

12:52.272 --> 12:54.207
BUT THAT GENERAL
WON'T TALK TO ME.

12:54.274 --> 12:58.245
AND I HAVE TRIED
EVERYTHING--PHONE CALLS,
EMAILS, SMOKE SIGNALS.

12:58.311 --> 13:01.181
MISS CROSE,
WE'D LIKE TO HELP YOU
CLEAN UP THIS MESS

13:01.248 --> 13:03.783
USING A VERY SPECIAL
TECHNIQUE.

13:03.851 --> 13:05.152
AND WHAT'S THAT, HON?

13:05.218 --> 13:07.320
[SLURPING]

13:07.387 --> 13:09.222
FRED, I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD HAVE

13:09.289 --> 13:11.658
WALKED OUT WITH THOSE
HEAT VISION GOGGLES.

13:11.724 --> 13:13.861
OH, I THINK I SHOULD HAVE.
LOOK!

13:13.927 --> 13:15.128
I DON'T SEE ANYTHING.

13:15.195 --> 13:17.164
BUT I CAN
WITH THESE GOGGLES.

13:17.230 --> 13:19.967
PUPPY PAW PRINTS.
AND THEY LEAD
TO THE GOLD ROOM.

13:20.033 --> 13:22.402
THEY ALSO LEAD
TO THE GOLD MONSTER!

13:22.469 --> 13:24.938
AAH!
AAH!

13:25.005 --> 13:26.940
MAN, THIS MAKES
THE ARMY LIFE

13:27.007 --> 13:28.608
LIKE NOT SO BAD.

13:28.675 --> 13:31.011
Fred: SHAGGY, SCOOBY,
RUN!

13:31.078 --> 13:33.113
I WONDER WHAT
THEY'RE RUNNING
FROM.

13:33.180 --> 13:36.183
[GROWL]

13:37.184 --> 13:39.586
ZOINKS!
LIKE I HAD TO ASK.

13:39.652 --> 13:40.954
AAH!
[GROWL]

13:41.021 --> 13:44.757
OH-OH-OH-OH-OH!

13:44.824 --> 13:47.660
LOOKS LIKE WE FINALLY
FOUND THE MESS HALL.

13:47.727 --> 13:48.828
AND SO DID HE!

13:48.896 --> 13:50.830
AH...AH...

13:50.898 --> 13:52.565
[WHIMPERING]

13:52.632 --> 13:56.736
[RUU RUU ARRR]

13:56.803 --> 13:59.372
NO!
NO!
NO!

14:11.451 --> 14:15.722
ZOINKS! LIKE,
14-KARAT...IS GOLD!

14:15.788 --> 14:18.058
Scooby: POOR PUPPY!

14:22.162 --> 14:24.164
WE'VE GOT TO SAVE
14-KARAT, AND FAST!

14:24.231 --> 14:25.465
[YIP YIP]
[RUFF RUFF]

14:25.532 --> 14:26.599
[ALARM]

14:26.666 --> 14:28.335
Velma:
WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:28.401 --> 14:29.502
[DOGS YIPPING]

14:29.569 --> 14:32.639
JUST WHAT IN THE NAME
OF THE 82nd AIRBORNE

14:32.705 --> 14:33.806
ARE YOU DOIN', MA'AM?

14:33.873 --> 14:35.842
I HAD NO OTHER CHOICE,
GENERAL.

14:35.909 --> 14:38.778
YOU WON'T MEET WITH ME.
YOU WON'T TALK TO ME.

14:38.845 --> 14:40.713
YOUR SILLY ARMY
EXPLOSIONS

14:40.780 --> 14:42.882
ARE GONNA PUT GOLD-ADE
OUTTA BUSINESS!

14:42.950 --> 14:46.954
FINE! I WILL MEET
WITH YOU...IN ARMY JAIL!

14:47.020 --> 14:49.122
TO THE STOCKADE!

14:49.189 --> 14:54.827
HUH. LOOKS LIKE
THE GOLD-ADE LADY HAS
A PROBLEM WITH THE GENERAL.

14:54.894 --> 14:56.729
LIKE, WE'VE GOT
OUR OWN PROBLEM--

14:56.796 --> 14:58.465
14-KARAT IS GOLD.

14:58.531 --> 14:59.799
WE CAN HELP HIM.

14:59.866 --> 15:02.069
FIRST WE HAVE TO FIND
THE GOLD MONSTER.

15:02.135 --> 15:03.937
WE'LL SAVE YA,
14-KARAT.

15:04.004 --> 15:05.538
DON'T MOVE!

15:06.940 --> 15:10.010
THE MONSTER SEEMS TO BE
COMING FROM THIS ROOM.

15:10.077 --> 15:11.744
Fred: SINCE THERE'S
NO OTHER WAY OUT,

15:11.811 --> 15:14.247
THIS TIME,
WE'LL STAY TOGETHER
AND LOOK FOR CLUES.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.920
LOOKS LIKE THERE IS
ANOTHER WAY OUT.

15:20.988 --> 15:24.057
GOOD WORK, SECRET SI--FIVE.

15:27.527 --> 15:30.998
IT SEEMS LIKE
SOMEONE'S MANAGED
TO BREAK INTO FORT KNOX.

15:31.064 --> 15:32.665
BUT THE GOLD'S
STILL HERE.

15:32.732 --> 15:36.203
HMM. MAYBE WE'LL
FIND OUT WHY AT THE
END OF THIS TUNNEL.

15:36.269 --> 15:37.670
[BOOM]

15:37.737 --> 15:40.673
LIKE, CAN WE JUST
FIND THE END THAT
GETS US OUTTA HERE?

15:51.084 --> 15:52.785
IS EVERYBODY
ALL RIGHT?

15:52.852 --> 15:54.454
LIKE, WE'RE OK!

15:54.521 --> 15:56.956
Fred: SHAGGY,
GO BACK TO THE GOLD ROOM.

15:57.024 --> 15:58.591
THERE WERE SOME MAPS
IN THE CORNER.

15:58.658 --> 16:01.128
MAYBE YOU CAN FIGURE
A WAY TO GET US
OUT OF HERE.

16:01.194 --> 16:04.131
ROGER THAT.
PUPS, LET'S MOVE OUT!

16:04.197 --> 16:05.965
Shaggy: HUP, HUP,
HUP, HAH,

16:06.033 --> 16:07.134
HUP, HUP, HUP.

16:07.200 --> 16:09.869
OK, PUPS.
WE HAVE A MISSION...

16:09.936 --> 16:12.905
AND THAT IS TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT ALL THESE LINES ARE.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.141
RAGGY!

16:14.207 --> 16:15.742
GOOD WORK, SCOOB!

16:15.808 --> 16:18.245
THESE AIR VENTS LEAD
RIGHT TO FRED, DAPHNE,
AND VELMA.

16:18.311 --> 16:21.248
BUT WE'RE TOO BIG
TO GO THROUGH.

16:21.314 --> 16:23.983
WAIT! I HAVE AN IDEA!

16:28.088 --> 16:30.190
GO GET 'EM!

16:41.101 --> 16:42.469
THIS DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

16:42.535 --> 16:44.771
IF SOMEONE WAS TRYING
TO BREAK INTO FORT KNOX,

16:44.837 --> 16:48.175
THIS TUNNEL SHOULD LEAD
TO THE BEGINNING,
BUT IT STOPS RIGHT HERE!

16:48.241 --> 16:50.443
MAYBE THE COLLAPSE
SEALED IT OFF.

16:52.779 --> 16:54.347
NICE LANDING, JINGLE.

16:55.715 --> 16:56.949
THANK YOU, BLING-BLING.

16:57.016 --> 16:58.785
NOW LET'S START DIGGING.

17:00.420 --> 17:04.124
UH, VELMA,
I THINK YOU'RE DIGGING
IN THE WRONG DIRECTION.

17:04.191 --> 17:07.927
IF MY SUSPICIONS ARE CORRECT...

17:07.994 --> 17:10.230
Fred: THE GOLD-ADE
FACTORY!

17:12.099 --> 17:13.633
HI, GUYS!

17:14.901 --> 17:17.070
WHEW! THAT'S
A LOTTA DIRT.

17:17.137 --> 17:19.939
I THINK I'VE JUST
SOLVED THE MYSTERY.

17:20.006 --> 17:22.542
NO ONE WAS TRYING
TO BREAK INTO FORT KNOX.

17:22.609 --> 17:25.078
SOMEONE WAS TRYING
TO BREAK OUT OF FORT KNOX.

17:25.145 --> 17:26.979
SOUNDS LIKE IT'S TIME
TO SET A TRAP.

17:27.046 --> 17:29.082
WE'LL NEED 2 GOOD MEN--

17:29.149 --> 17:31.851
SHAGGY, SCOOBY,
YOU'VE JUST BEEN DRAFTED.

17:31.918 --> 17:34.654
EVEN WITH
OUR LILY LIVERS
AND NO BACKBONES?

17:34.721 --> 17:37.890
LUCKILY,
THERE'S A CURE--
SCOOBY SNAX.

17:37.957 --> 17:39.759
AH!

17:52.205 --> 17:54.141
ATTENTION,
PRIVATE GOLD MAN!

17:54.207 --> 17:56.143
BECAUSE OF A BREACH
IN SECURITY,

17:56.209 --> 17:59.146
YOU NEED A NEW
ACCESS CARD--
LIKE THIS.

18:00.113 --> 18:02.014
ABOUT FACE. A-AT EASE.

18:02.081 --> 18:04.117
HALT! LIKE, RETREAT.

18:04.184 --> 18:06.286
LIKE, RETREAT!

18:14.961 --> 18:18.198
* THE GOAL WAS JUST BEYOND *

18:18.265 --> 18:20.333
* I'M PRESSIN' ON *

18:20.400 --> 18:22.402
* I'M PRESSIN' ON *

18:22.469 --> 18:24.704
* OR MY DISTRESS
IS GOING TO GET ME *

18:24.771 --> 18:28.208
* I'M PRESSIN' ON,
PRESSIN' ON *

18:28.275 --> 18:30.243
* AND I WON'T SIT BACK *

18:30.310 --> 18:32.212
* AND TAKE THIS ANYMORE *

18:32.279 --> 18:34.113
* 'CAUSE AS I WENT BACK *

18:34.181 --> 18:36.048
* I GOT ONE FOR
THE GROUP TO SCORE *

18:36.115 --> 18:39.252
* AND TO ACT THE WAY I WAS
WOULD JUST BE WRONG *

18:39.319 --> 18:42.322
* I'M PRESSIN' ON *

18:44.424 --> 18:46.993
HOO HOO HOO HAH HAH HAH!

18:47.059 --> 18:50.630
HEE HEE HAH HAH HAH HAH!
HAH HAH HAH!

18:50.697 --> 18:54.267
ALL RIGHT, GANG.
LET'S GO FOR THE GOLD.
NOW!

18:59.639 --> 19:01.908
NOW WE'LL FIND OUT
WHAT KIND OF PERSON

19:01.974 --> 19:06.078
TRAINS NICE LITTLE PUPPIES
TO DO THEIR NASTY
DIRTY WORK!

19:06.145 --> 19:09.682
LET'S SEE WHO WANTED
TO BREAK OUT OF FORT KNOX.

19:10.550 --> 19:12.185
All: DRILL SERGEANT PAYNE?!

19:12.252 --> 19:14.221
BUT, LIKE, WHY?

19:14.287 --> 19:16.889
THIS ARMY MAN
WANTED TO BE A BUSINESSMAN

19:16.956 --> 19:18.925
AND TAKE OVER GOLD-ADE.

19:18.991 --> 19:20.960
BY CAUSING EXPLOSIONS
EVERY HOUR,

19:21.027 --> 19:22.729
HE COULD DRIVE
SUE CROSE AWAY.

19:22.795 --> 19:25.432
THEN ALL HE NEEDED
WERE THE SECRET INGREDIENTS,

19:25.498 --> 19:28.435
AND HE'D BE
THE SOLID-GOLD
SOFT DRINK KING.

19:28.501 --> 19:30.570
AND I WOULD HAVE
GOTTEN OUT OF FORT KNOX,
TOO,

19:30.637 --> 19:33.973
IF IT WEREN'T FOR
YOU MEDDLING CIVILIANS,
SIRS AND MA'AMS!

19:34.040 --> 19:37.477
HE TRAINED THE SECRET 6
TO STAY UP AT NIGHT
AND DIG THAT TUNNEL.

19:37.544 --> 19:39.712
THAT EXPLAINS THE DIRT
ON THEIR PAWS,

19:39.779 --> 19:42.449
BUT WHY THE UGLY
GOLD PLASMA SUIT?

19:42.515 --> 19:44.651
SO HE COULD BLEND
INTO THE GOLD.

19:44.717 --> 19:47.220
BECAUSE WITH SECURITY
THIS TIGHT,

19:47.287 --> 19:49.822
THE BEST PLACE TO HIDE
IS IN PLAIN SIGHT.

19:49.889 --> 19:52.259
[PUPPIES YIPPING]

19:54.093 --> 19:57.129
RIGHT. 14-KARAT
IS STILL GOLD.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.332
HE'S FINE, SIR!

19:59.399 --> 20:02.502
IT'S A GOLD VARIATION
OF THE SHUT-DOWN GOO, SIR!

20:02.569 --> 20:05.605
IT PEELS RIGHT OFF, SIR!

20:07.774 --> 20:09.609
[GIGGLING]

20:09.676 --> 20:12.011
WELL, WE GOTTA HAND IT
TO THE SECRET 6.

20:12.078 --> 20:14.747
WITHOUT THEM,
WE'D STILL BE TRAPPED
IN THAT TUNNEL.

20:14.814 --> 20:18.518
THEY'RE LIKE HEROES.
YOU KNOW WHAT
THEY DESERVE?

20:25.858 --> 20:28.295
ABOUT...FACE.

20:28.361 --> 20:30.297
* SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOOBY-DOO *

20:30.363 --> 20:32.532
[RUFF RUFF RUFF RUFF
RUFF RUFF RUFF *

20:32.599 --> 20:34.567
* SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOOBY-DOO *

20:34.634 --> 20:38.705
SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOO!
HEE HEE HEE!
